Categories: Structured Text Processing -> Operation on Primitives -> Numbers -> List
Definition: In this task you will be given a list of numbers. You should remove any number that is not an integer (whole number). If every number is not an whole number then an empty list ("[]") should be returned. Otherwise, answer with the list of whole numbers separated by comma inside brackets.

Positive Examples.explanation: 7 and 11 are the only whole numbers in the list.
Every value in the input list is not an integer, so an empty list is returned.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output contains only numbers that are not integers.
The output rounded all of the non integers to the closest integer.
The output split the integers and non-integers into separate lists.
Your answer should be in brackets.
